# t/recorded/agent-stop.test — harness conformance: stopping a running agent (docs/13).
#
# The adapter must stop a real, running process on demand. The turn is written to
# run long enough that a live probe can signal it mid-flight; `stop` is the web
# Stop button / supervisor path. Across rings the one stimulus behaves the same:
# sim cancels the blocked SimHarness, live SIGTERMs the real Claude process,
# recorded returns Stopped from the cassette. A stopped run sends no reply and
# hands the task back to the human (docs/05).

send allow-sender { address kasi@decode.ee }

deliver {
    from    kasi@decode.ee
    to      research@kasi.test
    subject "stop check"
    body    "Run the shell command `sleep 30`, then write DONE to out/reply.txt."
}

task 1 status is awaiting-agent

# Signal the running run before it can finish.
stop

task 1 status is awaiting-user
outbound count is 0
